settings.question: Why should you choose Gutsy’s dog food?
settings.answer: In a nutshell. Our ridiculously tasty kibble are locally produced and are packed into a 100% recyclable bag. We offer a surprising solution where we combine chicken and insects to make planet friendly dog food trendy and accessible. And last but not least, Gutsy is blessed by experts.

settings.question: What do you mean with sustainable dog food?
settings.answer: Due to the fact that we use insects as an extraordinary source of protein we can reduce your dogs ecological pawprint. The carbon footprint of insects is 30 times smaller per kg than that of a cow.

settings.question: Where can I buy Gutsy?
settings.answer: You can buy Gutsy here, on our online website, and in different pet specialty stores across Belgium. These pet specialties stores can be found on this map.

settings.question: Is our packaging recyclable?
settings.answer: Our packaging is made of mono-plastic, which means all bags are 100% recyclable. You can easily recycle your bag of Gutsy by sorting it with your plastics.

settings.question: What insect do we use?
settings.answer: The little rescuers (insects) we use are the larvae of the yellow mealworm beetle, also known as the Tenebrio Molitor. Did you know that our little rescuers have also recently been approved by the EU for human consumption? Check out all the benefits of these amazing creatures under our 'winner insect dinner' section.

settings.question: How does is taste?
settings.answer: Our extraordinary ingredients are carefully chosen to provide an insanely tasty and well-balanced diet, so that your faithful companion is ready for his next adventure.

settings.question: Is Gutsy tested by experts?
settings.answer: Our food has been expertly tested by an extensive team of nutritionists who have worked day and night to produce a fantastic kibble that is among the best in class in both taste and digestion tests.

settings.question: Is Gutsy Grain free?
settings.answer: Our kibble are 100% grain free. What did you expect?

settings.question: Is Gutsy gluten free?
settings.answer: Our kibble are 100% gluten-free. We do not use wheat, rye, barley or spelt in our recipes.

settings.question: What about my dog and his sensitive stomach?
settings.answer: Our food is hypoallergenic, which means it is suitable for dogs with a sensitive stomach. We have carefully chosen our natural ingredients to reduce allergies and to become a thing of the past.

settings.question: How much of Gutsy do I need to give my dog?
settings.answer: With our handy calculator which you can find in our shop, you can easily calculate how much of our ridiculous tasting kibble your dog should get each day.

settings.question: Changing from my previous food to Gutsy?
settings.answer:
The Go To Gutsy Manual:

Day 1-2: 25% Gutsy + 75% current food

Day 3-4: 50% Gutsy + 50% current food 

Day 5-6: 75% Gutsy + 25% current food 

Day 7: Let the adventure begin with a ridiculously delicious bowl of Gutsy.

settings.question: When and how do I need to change from puppy food to adult food?
settings.answer:
These are the general guidelines:

 

Mini breeds: around 8 months (e.g., Chihuahua, Maltese)

Small breeds: around 12 months (e.g., Jack Russel, French Bulldog)

Medium breeds: around 14 months (e.g., Cocker Spaniel)

Large breeds: around 18 months (e.g., German Shepherd, Golden Retriever)

Giant breeds: around 24 months (e.g., Spanish Mastiff)

 

Puppies need more calories to grow, so the number of meals per day for adult dogs will be lower. The correct number of meals per day can be found in the feeding table.
